Advanced CMS Schema
Full Entity & Field Specification
Travel Platform — Admin Panel & Website Builder
v2.0  ·  2025

1. Overview & Design Principles
This document defines the complete advanced schema for all CMS entities in the travel platform. Every entity that has a public URL — Country, Region, Destination (Trek), Tour, Activity, and Package — shares a standardised set of blocks for SEO, media, and FAQs, while also carrying its own product-specific fields.

1.1  Shared Blocks (Applied to All Entities)
The following blocks appear on every entity. Rather than duplicating fields, each entity stores a reference to these block structures as embedded JSON columns or separate related tables:
•	SEO Settings — meta title, description, keywords, OG tags, canonical URL, robots directives, JSON-LD structured data
•	Media — bannerImage (16:9), cardImage (3:2), ogImage (1.91:1), galleryImages[ ]
•	FAQs — ordered list of question/answer pairs with active toggle
•	Group Discounts — tiered pricing by group size (percentage or fixed-amount off)

1.2  Entity Hierarchy
Country → Region → Destination (Trek) / Tour / Activity / Package
Packages are independent of the region hierarchy — they can link multiple destinations across different regions and carry their own custom itinerary, price, and group discount structure.

Note: All slug fields are auto-generated from the title/name on creation and should not be edited manually unless a redirect is configured.

 
2. Shared Block Specifications
2.1  SEO Settings Block
Every entity stores an embedded seo JSON object (or a separate seo_settings table with a polymorphic FK). The following fields apply to all entity types.

Field	Type	Required	Description / Notes
metaTitle	string	No	SEO title tag. Max 60 chars. Falls back to entity title if empty.
metaDescription	string	No	Meta description. Max 160 chars. Falls back to truncated description.
metaKeywords	string[]	No	Array of keyword strings for keyword meta tag.
ogTitle	string	No	Open Graph title. Falls back to metaTitle.
ogDescription	string	No	Open Graph description. Falls back to metaDescription.
ogImage	string	No	URL of OG share image. Recommended ratio 1.91:1 (1200x630px).
canonicalUrl	string	No	Explicit canonical URL. Auto-generated from slug if blank.
noIndex	boolean	No	Exclude from search engine indexing. Default false.
noFollow	boolean	No	Prevent crawling of outbound links. Default false.
structuredData	JSON	No	Custom JSON-LD schema markup (e.g. TouristDestination, TouristAttraction).

Tip: metaTitle and metaDescription are the two highest-priority SEO fields. Always populate them in the admin panel. Leaving them blank causes the site to fall back to the entity title/description, which may exceed recommended character limits.

2.2  Media Fields Block
Image URLs are stored as strings pointing to the CDN or object storage path. The admin panel enforces ratio validation at upload time with crop guidance.

Field	Type	Required	Description / Notes
bannerImage	string (URL)	No	Hero/banner image. Recommended ratio 16:9 (1920x1080px min). Displayed at full width on page headers.
cardImage	string (URL)	No	Card/thumbnail image. Recommended ratio 3:2 (600x400px min). Used in listing grids and search results.
ogImage	string (URL)	No	Social share preview image. Ratio 1.91:1 (1200x630px). Separate from bannerImage.
galleryImages	string[]	No	Array of image URLs for photo gallery/carousel. No fixed limit but 8–16 recommended.
altText	string	No	Alt text for bannerImage (accessibility + SEO).
cardImageAlt	string	No	Alt text for cardImage.

Image Field	Ratio	Recommended Size	Where Used
bannerImage	16 : 9	1920 × 1080 px	Page hero headers, full-width banners
cardImage	3 : 2	600 × 400 px	Listing grids, search results, related cards
ogImage	1.91 : 1	1200 × 630 px	Social media share previews (Facebook, Twitter, WhatsApp)
galleryImages[]	Any (prefer 16:9)	1280 × 720 px min	Photo gallery / image carousel on detail page

2.3  FAQs Block
Each entity supports an ordered list of FAQ items stored as a separate faqs table (polymorphic) or as a JSON array column.

Field	Type	Required	Description / Notes
question	string	Yes	The FAQ question text.
answer	string	Yes	The answer body. Supports rich text / markdown.
sortOrder	integer	No	Display order (ascending). Default 0.
isActive	boolean	No	Show/hide this FAQ without deleting. Default true.

Tip: FAQs are rendered on the public page and also injected into the entity's JSON-LD structured data as FAQPage schema, improving search snippet visibility.

2.4  Group Discounts Block
All product types — Destination (Trek), Tour, Activity, and Package — support tiered group discounts. Discounts are applied on top of the base price during checkout. Multiple tiers can be configured (e.g. 5–9 pax: 5% off, 10–15 pax: 10% off, 16+ pax: 15% off).

Field	Type	Required	Description / Notes
minPax	integer	Yes	Minimum number of people to qualify for this tier.
maxPax	integer	No	Maximum people for this tier. Null = no upper limit.
discountType	enum	Yes	Values: percentage | fixed_amount
discountValue	decimal(10,2)	Yes	Percentage (0–100) or fixed currency amount.
label	string	No	Human-friendly tier name (e.g. 'Family Group', 'School Group').
isActive	boolean	No	Enable/disable tier without deleting. Default true.

Note: Tiers must not overlap in their pax ranges. The admin panel should validate that (minPax of tier N+1) > (maxPax of tier N). If maxPax is null on a tier, no further tiers may be added.

Tier Label	Min Pax	Max Pax	Discount Type	Discount Value
Small Group	2	4	percentage	5%
Family Group	5	9	percentage	8%
School / Club	10	19	percentage	12%
Large Group	20	(no limit)	percentage	18%

Example above: A booking for 12 people on a trek priced at $500/person would receive 12% off, bringing the price to $440/person.

 
