7.2  Activity Link Modes
The linkMode field determines how and where an activity is displayed on the website:

linkMode	Behaviour	Admin Configuration
standalone	Activity has its own dedicated page (/activities/paragliding-pokhara). Appears in activity listings and global search.	No linkedTrekIds or linkedTourIds required.
destination	Activity is shown as a section on one or more Destination pages (linked via linkedTrekIds). No standalone URL generated.	Set linkedTrekIds[] to one or more Destination IDs.
product	Activity is bundled within a Tour or Package. Shown in the product's inclusions section.	Set linkedTourIds[] or linked via TourActivity junction.
multi	Activity appears both as standalone AND on linked destinations/products. Maximum visibility mode.	Set standalone=true, and populate both linkedTrekIds and/or linkedTourIds.

