10. Database Implementation Notes
10.1  SEO & Media Storage Strategy
Option A (recommended for flexibility): Store SEO and media as embedded JSON columns on each entity table. This avoids joins and simplifies API responses.
•	seo JSON column on each entity table: { metaTitle, metaDescription, metaKeywords, ogTitle, ogDescription, ogImage, canonicalUrl, noIndex, noFollow, structuredData }
•	media JSON column: { bannerImage, cardImage, ogImage, galleryImages, altText, cardImageAlt }

Option B (recommended for shared media management): Polymorphic seo_settings and media_assets tables with entityType and entityId columns, allowing a centralised media library with reuse across entities.

10.2  FAQs Table
Recommended as a separate polymorphic table for query flexibility and ordering:
•	faqs ( id UUID PK, entityType VARCHAR 50, entityId UUID, question TEXT, answer TEXT, sortOrder INT DEFAULT 0, isActive BOOLEAN DEFAULT true, createdAt TIMESTAMP, updatedAt TIMESTAMP )
•	Index on (entityType, entityId, isActive, sortOrder) for efficient page queries.

10.3  Group Discounts Table
Separate table with polymorphic entity reference:
•	group_discounts ( id UUID PK, entityType VARCHAR 50, entityId UUID, minPax INT, maxPax INT NULLABLE, discountType VARCHAR 20, discountValue DECIMAL(10,2), label VARCHAR 100 NULLABLE, isActive BOOLEAN DEFAULT true, createdAt TIMESTAMP, updatedAt TIMESTAMP )
•	Constraint: no overlapping pax ranges per (entityType, entityId) combination.

10.4  Package Destinations Join Table
•	package_destinations ( id UUID PK, packageId UUID FK, destinationId UUID FK, customName VARCHAR 255 NULLABLE, customDescription TEXT NULLABLE, durationDays INT NULLABLE, sortOrder INT DEFAULT 0 )
•	Unique constraint on (packageId, destinationId) to prevent duplicate destination entries within a package.

10.5  Activity Link Tables
•	activity_treks ( activityId UUID FK, trekId UUID FK, sortOrder INT ) — links activities to destination pages
•	activity_tours ( activityId UUID FK, tourId UUID FK, sortOrder INT ) — links activities to tour products
•	Both are junction tables with composite PK on (activityId, trekId) and (activityId, tourId) respectively.

 
